{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CD6scuQmbKD5Nfx88VH7BS","type":"tool_result","content":"   490â†’\n   491â†’/* Drawer */\n   492â†’.drawer {\n   493â†’    position: fixed;\n   494â†’    top: 0;\n   495â†’    right: -420px;\n   496â†’    width: 400px;\n   497â†’    height: 100vh;\n   498â†’    background: var(--bg-surface);\n   499â†’    border-left: 1px solid var(--border);\n   500â†’    box-shadow: -4px 0 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n   501â†’    transition: right 0.25s ease;\n   502â†’    z-index: 100;\n   503â†’    display: flex;\n   504â†’    flex-direction: column;\n   505â†’    overflow: hidden;\n   506â†’}\n   507â†’\n   508â†’.drawer.drawer-open { right: 0; }\n   509â†’\n   510â†’.drawer-header {\n   511â†’    display: flex;\n   512â†’    justify-content: space-between;\n   513â†’    align-items: center;\n   514â†’    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;\n   515â†’    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n   516â†’    font-weight: 700;\n   517â†’    font-size: 1rem;\n   518â†’}\n   519â†’\n   520â†’.drawer-close {\n   521â†’    background: none;\n   522â†’    border: none;\n   523â†’    font-size: 1.4rem;\n   524â†’    cursor: pointer;\n   525â†’    color: var(--text-muted);\n   526â†’    padding: 0 0.25rem;\n   527â†’}\n   528â†’\n   529â†’.drawer-close:hover { color: var(--text); }\n   530â†’\n   531â†’.drawer-body {\n   532â†’    padding: 1rem;\n   533â†’    overflow-y: auto;\n   534â†’    flex: 1;\n   535â†’}\n   536â†’\n   537â†’.drawer-body pre {\n   538â†’    background: var(--bg);\n   539â†’    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n   540â†’    border-radius: var(--radius);\n   541â†’    padding: 0.75rem;\n   542â†’    font-family: var(--mono);\n   543â†’    font-size: 0.8rem;\n   544â†’    max-height: 400px;"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a37f3516-6a98-45b4-b440-44c340a4d486","uuid":"f1cc5a3d-38ba-4e9f-8961-063533a63b76","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css","content":"\n/* Drawer */\n.drawer {\n    position: fixed;\n    top: 0;\n    right: -420px;\n    width: 400px;\n    height: 100vh;\n    background: var(--bg-surface);\n    border-left: 1px solid var(--border);\n    box-shadow: -4px 0 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n    transition: right 0.25s ease;\n    z-index: 100;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    overflow: hidden;\n}\n\n.drawer.drawer-open { right: 0; }\n\n.drawer-header {\n    display: flex;\n    justify-content: space-between;\n    align-items: center;\n    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;\n    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n    font-weight: 700;\n    font-size: 1rem;\n}\n\n.drawer-close {\n    background: none;\n    border: none;\n    font-size: 1.4rem;\n    cursor: pointer;\n    color: var(--text-muted);\n    padding: 0 0.25rem;\n}\n\n.drawer-close:hover { color: var(--text); }\n\n.drawer-body {\n    padding: 1rem;\n    overflow-y: auto;\n    flex: 1;\n}\n\n.drawer-body pre {\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border: 1px solid var(--border);\n    border-radius: var(--radius);\n    padding: 0.75rem;\n    font-family: var(--mono);\n    font-size: 0.8rem;\n    max-height: 400px;","numLines":55,"startLine":490,"totalLines":577}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GNJptQuYzLJ6kyFujWA8yp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The styling looks fine. Let me think about this differently. Maybe the issue is a race condition or a promise handling issue in the JavaScript.\n\nActually, let me look at the config values that come from the workflows API. When the `apiStepDef` has `Config map[string]string`, and the step config has `prompt = file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`, the JSON will be:\n\n```json\n{\"config\": {\"prompt\": \"file(\\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\")\"}}\n```\n\nWait no, in Go's `map[string]string`, the values are Go strings. When JSON-marshaled, the inner double quotes get escaped. \n\nSo the JSON value for prompt would be: `\"file(\\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\")\"`. But that depends on whether the Go string itself contains literal double quotes. Let me trace through what the parser actually storesâ€”it reads the raw characters from `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` and keeps them as-is in the string value.\n\nWhen JSON-encodes this, those literal quote characters get escaped to `\\\"`, so the JSON becomes `\"file(\\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\")\"`. Then when JavaScript parses it back from JSON, `step.config.prompt` becomes the string `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")` with actual double-quote characters in it, which the frontend displays in the metadata.\n\nI've been going in circles trying to find a subtle bug here. Let me shift focus and check if `handleAPIStepContent` has a more fundamental issue I'm overlooking. Let me trace through the \"test\" step with `run = \"go test ./... 2>&1\"` one more time to see where things might be breaking down. I'm realizing there's a potential issue with how quoted values are being handled â€” when `parseValue` processes a `file(\"...\")` expression, it keeps the quotes intact in the stored config, but for string literals like `\"go test ./...\"` it strips them. Let me trace through the parsing logic to see if this inconsistency affects how the prompt file path gets resolved. I'm seeing a mismatch between how the parser and mutator handle string values. The parser strips quotes from `max_attempts = \"2\"` to store just `2`, but the mutator test expects the Config to contain `\"2\"` with quotes included. I need to figure out whether the Config should store the raw quoted string or the parsed value, and ensure both directions are consistent. For the `run` config with `\"go test ./... 2>&1\"`, the parser extracts just the string content without the surrounding quotes. I'm wondering if the issue is that certain config values are being stored with quotes when they shouldn't be, or if there's something specific about how the daemon handles file paths. Let me step back and look at the actual git diff to see what changed.\n\nActually, rereading the taskâ€”the workflow view shows filenames when you click steps but doesn't load the content. That's the real problem to solve. The backend could be returning a 404 if the file path doesn't resolve, the API route might not be matching correctly, or there's a JavaScript bug on the frontend. Let me check the route registration again and trace through what URL the frontend is actually requesting.\n\nThe backend registers the endpoint at `GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content`, and the frontend constructs the URL by encoding the project, workflow, and step names. The paths match up, but I should verify how Go's path wildcards handle step names with hyphensâ€”they should work fine since hyphens are valid in path segments. Let me check what `PathValue` is actually returning.\n\nI'm realizing there might be an issue with how the config values are being parsed. The `parseValue` function returns the string content without quotes, so `step.Config[\"run\"]` should be `\"go test ./... 2>&1\"` without extra quotes. But in the mutator test, the config map has quoted values like `\"prompt\": file(\"prompts/review.md\")` and `\"max_attempts\": \"` which looks incomplete.\n\nLet me check the parser test to understand whether quoted values are being stored with or without their surrounding quotes.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":709,"cache_read_input_tokens":52663,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":709},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a37f3516-6a98-45b4-b440-44c340a4d486","uuid":"99dacdae-565b-4fef-86d9-2302a677c4bc"}
